{
  "stem": "6052.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The hatred and the problems which aroused for-- for Jews and were enhanced at that time were absolutely insurmountable.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But I want to dwell another few minutes on the past in Leipzig, what still is in my mind.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And when I went through some kind of historical resume by a book which was written in Leipzig, then I come across names which show me what I-- past, what I remember, what I could remember.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "There were so many charitable Jews who helped people, Jews and not Jews, like Chaim [INAUDIBLE] in 1928, and there was one other wonderful person, [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We erected a large building, at that time the largest building in the city of Leipzig and maybe even in the country.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Here, we are now used to skyscrapers, but at that time, this was a big, big event.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And the house was called [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "It still stands.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And I revisited it 1988.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And then, to later year in 1931, I remember-- I speak now what made me remember when I read about it-- an altersheim-- and then as youngster, I remember altersheim, why it was connected to very good people and known people in Leipzig, to Jews and non-Jews alike.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "It was founded by one who owned a large department-- apartment-- house for merchandise.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "[INAUDIBLE] And if I'm not mistaken, his name was [INAUDIBLE], and his wife was a founder of this altersheim, which is an old age home.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And then was a foundation of one of the greatest hospitals at that time.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "It was modern at that time.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "This was the most modern hospital, which was established by Jews-- [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And I remember these names very well.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Before my father escaped-- he not escaped.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
